Privacy Policy for AutoHazer
Effective Date: 19-Oct-2024

     AutoHazer is committed to protecting your privacy. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and share your information when you use our software application.

1. Information We Collect
     We may collect the following information when you use AutoHazer: Your name, email address, and profile information when you sign in using your Google, Facebook, or Apple account.
Zoom Meeting ID and passcode that you input to join a Zoom meeting through AutoHazer.

2. How We Use Your Information
     We use the information we collect to: Allow you to sign in and authenticate using your Google, Facebook, or Apple account.
Automatically join Zoom meetings for you with the provided credentials.
We do not share or sell your information to third parties.

3. Data Storage
     We store your data securely within the application to ensure that your information is protected. We do not store your data on any external servers.

4. Your Rights
     You have the right to access, modify, or delete your personal information within AutoHazer. If you wish to do so, please contact us.

5. Contact Us
     If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please contact us at: Email:sandrusimsone13579@gmail.com
